Stonington C-Hub Organizational Information \- DRAFT  
Feb. 2025

MISSION *\- The Island Connectivity Hub provides Deer Isle, Stonington and the surrounding coastal region with the community connections, tools, skills, and resources to continue to thrive in the face of change.*

KEY PRIORITIES OF THE CONNECTIVITY HUB  
Supports:

* *The Blue Economy (ToS)*  
* *Digital Literacy (MCA)*   
* *Health and Wellness goals for fishermen (MCA, NEC, MCCF)*  
* *Education and Workforce Pathways (MCA, Adult Ed/PL, Haystack)*   
  * *High school completion*  
  * *College/career access or transitions*  
  * *Create community through hands-on learning*  
  * *Provide trainings and resources for fishermen and fishing families, with a focus on financial resiliency* 

Provides:

* *Structure for community partners to work together (All \- Hub/Spoke)*  
* *Resources for partner organizations to help us all improve (All \- Hub/Spoke)*  
  * *C-Hub provides a physical space as well as a broader sense of regional connection (All \- Hub/Spoke)*

The Stonington C-Hub is a *Conduit. It helps community partners work In Concert with each other and fosters Coordination, Cooperation and Collaboration.*

2\. Written Description of Org Structure:

* CORE GROUP  
  * Town of Stonington \- organizing leader through 2025?, fiscal agent  
  * Island Institute \- Project Management through 2026  
  * Lead Partners in the Building  
    * Deer Isle Adult and Community Education \- anticipated primary leader starting in 2026  
    * Northeast Center for Occupational Health and Safety (NEC) \- community health worker  
    * Haystack Mountain School of Crafts/Fab-Lab \- maker space (2025)  
* CORE GROUP PLUS+  
  * Maine Center for Coastal Fisheries \- closely tied to NEC  
  * Project Launch \- closely tied to Adult Ed  
  * Haystack Mountain School of Crafts/Fab-Lab \- maker space (2026)  
* COMMUNITY PARTNERS  
  * Healthy Island Project  
  * Stonington Library  
  * Chase Memorial Library  
  * Island Health and Wellness  
  * The Community Center  
  * The Chamber of Commerce  
  * New partners \- TBD
